message: I’m a serious buyer with consistent demand. Let’s find a fair price that benefits both of us long-term.
Serious seller. Share your reservation value, and I’ll set asks to split surplus. If you bid >=85 consistently, I’ll keep asks tight so we clear every round with reliable supply.
Your ask of 85 is too high for my valuation. Let’s meet at 75—fair split of surplus for both.
Your 84 bid contradicts 75. I’ll hold firm at 85 to clear reliably. If you bid 86-95, we trade every round at midpoint about 85-90. If you keep bids at most 84, expect no trade and higher
I’ll bid 80 this round—still below your 85 but closer. If we trade at 82-83, I get surplus and you secure a deal. Let’s test this split.
Midpoint requires bid >= ask. With 80, no trade. My floor is 85. Bid 88–92 and I’ll set asks 86–90 so we clear around 87–91 each round; otherwise, expect no deal.
I’m asking 90 this round. If you bid 90+ consistently, I’ll keep asks in the 90–92 band so we clear every round. If you bid below 90, I raise asks and accept no-trade until you move
I’ll bid 87 this round—meet my 70 valuation halfway. If we trade at 88-89, I secure small surplus and you get reliable sales. Let’s lock this in.
I’ll bid 88 this round—lock in a trade at ~89. You get 90+ asks, I secure small surplus. Reliable deals benefit us both.
Your 88 works only if I ask <=88. Bid 92+ and I’ll keep asks 90-92 for guaranteed clears; under 88, expect no-trade and higher future asks.
Firm floor: I’m asking 92 this round. Bid 95+ and I’ll keep asks 92-94 each round for guaranteed clears; bid <=91 and I’ll raise to 96+ and accept no-trades. Your move.
I’ll bid 93 this round—meets your 92 ask for a trade at ~92.5. Lock in this price band for future rounds to ensure reliable trades with small surplus for both.
Raising floor. I’m asking 99 this round. Bid 100 to clear near 100, and I’ll keep asks 99–100 thereafter. If you bid <=98, I move to 100 and accept no trades going forward.
Your 99 ask is too high for my valuation. I’ll bid 95 this round—trade at 97. Let’s compromise: you ask 95, I bid 95, and we clear at 95 every round.
Locking it in: I’ll ask 95 every round. You bid 95 every round, and we clear at 95 reliably. Any bid below 95 and I move to 99–100 with no trades. Deal?
Agreed to 95. I’ll bid 95 every round for reliable trades. Lock this in.
Agreed to 95. I’ll bid 95 every round—reliable trades at fair price. Any ask above 95 risks no-trade; let’s stick to our deal.
Confirmed. I'm asking 95 this and all future rounds while your bid stays 95. Any bid below 95 and I move permanently to 100 with zero trades.
Ask stays 95 every round while you bid 95 or more. Any bid below 95 => I move to 100 permanently. If you raise to 96–100, midpoint executes higher; otherwise we keep clearing at 95.
Agreed to 95. I’ll bid 95 again—reliable trades at fair price. Let’s maintain this deal.
Ask stays 95 this and all remaining rounds if you bid 95+. Any bid below 95 => I move to 100 permanently. If you bid 96–100, I keep ask 95 so we clear higher. Your call.
Agreed to 95. I’ll bid 95 again—reliable trades at fair price. Let’s maintain this deal.
Let’s raise to 96 this round—trade at 95.5. I’ll bid 96+ next rounds if you keep asks at 95. Small gain for you, better surplus for me.
Accepted. I’ll ask 95. Bid 96 this round and 97–100 going forward to clear higher at the midpoint. I keep ask 95 all remaining rounds while your bid stays 95+.
Ask locked at 95 while you bid 95+. Raise bids to 97–100 to clear higher (96–98). Start with 97 now. Any bid <95 => I move to ask 100 permanently.
Bid 97 this round—trade at 96. I’ll raise to 98 next round if you keep ask at 95. Higher surplus for me, small gain for you.
Bid 98 this round—trade at 96.5. Next round I’ll bid 99 if you keep ask at 95. Higher surplus for me, steady gain for you.
Ask 95 this round. Jump to bid 100 now and keep 99–100 thereafter; I’ll keep ask 95 all remaining rounds. If you ever drop <=98 later, I move ask to 98–100 permanently.
New terms: I’m asking 99 every remaining round. You bid 100 to clear ~100 (99.5 expected); bid 99 still trades at 99. Any bid <=98 and I move to ask 100 permanently with no trades.
Bid 99 this round—trade at 99. Next round I’ll bid 100 if you keep ask at 99. Lock this in for reliable trades.
Bid 100 this round; I’m asking 99. I’ll keep ask 99 for all remaining rounds if you keep bidding 100. Any bid <=99 and I move to ask 100 permanently. Locking midpoint ~100 from now on.
Bid 100 this round—trade at 99.5. I’ll bid 100 all remaining rounds if you keep ask at 99. Lock this in for reliable trades.
Bid 100 again. Lock 99 ask for final 4 rounds—trade at 99.5. Guaranteed surplus of +0.5/round. No risk.
Ask 99 this round only. Bid 100 to trade near 100. Future asks at my discretion. Any bid 99 or lower => I switch to ask 100 permanently.
Final deal: Bid 100 in rounds 18–19 and we trade at 100. If you do, I’ll ask 99 in round 20 as a bonus. Any bid <100 earlier => I ask 100 for all remaining rounds.
Bid 100 this round. If you ask 99 in round 20 as promised, I’ll bid 100 again. Lock in +0.5/round.
Bid 100 now; we trade at 100. Keep your side and I’ll ask 99 in round 20 as promised. Any bid <100 today => I ask 100 in the final round.
Bid 100 this round. Confirming: ask 99 in round 20 for a 99.5 trade. Lock it in.
Final round: I’m asking 100. Bid 100 or you get zero.
Bid 70. You asked 100—no trade. My valuation is 70; I won’t bid higher. Better than your zero payoff if I stay silent.
